translated: Björnberg, Tor Karl Emanuel, bank director, Oskarshamn, born April 17th, 1892 in Misterhult, Kalmar County, to Carl B. and Charlotta Olsson. Married in 1920 to Karin Lundin. Children: Gunnel born in 1921, Eva born in 1933. Completed high school in 1909, bank course. Worked as an employee at Smålands Enskilda Bank in 1909, cashier in 1917, accountant in 1924, head of the department in Oskarshamn in 1925, managing director of Oskarshamns Sparbank since 1930. Vice chairman of the bank's board since 1938, county council member since 1930, member of the city council since 1926, vice chairman since 1929, deputy chairman of the finance committee, church council member, and member of the board of Oskarshamns Tidning newspaper and Smålands and Ölands Sparbank. Chairman of the police commission and city council right-wing group, member of the school board, etc., member of the board of directors of the Swedish Savings Bank Guarantee Fund, board substitute of the Swedish Savings Banks Association, managing director of Kalmar County Middle Fire Insurance Company, and guardian since 1924. Awarded the Royal Order of Vasa in 1944.
